ser}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/SergioBenitez/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-11-12T06:44:46Z","updated_at":"2022-11-12T11:41:16Z","body":"So one of these is a bug, the other is a consequence.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> In some cases wrong field name is returned in the error.\r\n\r\nThis is a bug, and fixed by https://github.com/SergioBenitez/Rocket/commit/8166ad0c7c12ca9a247b38a2273c7c598e06aee6.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> All errors are not returned.\r\n\r\nThis is not a bug. Validation happens in three stages:\r\n  1. The value is converted via `FromForm`, which may fail. (say, into a `u64`).\r\n  2. _Local_ ad-hoc validators, those that don't depend on other fields, are run.\r\n  3. _Global_ validators, those that _do_ depends on other fields, are run.\r\n\r\nIf there are errors at any stage, they are returned without the remaining validation stages running.\r\n\r\nThe separation of stages 2 and 3 is documented in the [guide](https://rocket.rs/v0.5-rc/guide/requests/#ad-hoc-validation), though not clearly, and it also isn't reflected in the API docs.\r\n\r\nStage 2 simply cannot run if stage 1 fails because a value of the given type is not available. Stages 2 and 3 _can_ ostensibly be flattened into a single stage which would yield the results expected in the original post. I'm looking into whether there's any issue with doing this as I do agree this is likely the more expected and useful result.","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.g